  "text": "Definition A scattering first-order transform [CITATION_1] is defined from a mother wavelet ψ and a low-pass filter φ. An input signal x is filtered by a collection of dilated band-pass wavelets obtained from ψ, followed by a modulus and finally averaged by a dilation of φ. The wavelets we chose decompose the signal in a basis in which transient structure of a signal is represented more compactly. We describe the construction of each filter and justify the necessity of each operator.",
